eBay Inc's eBay Enterprise And OrderGroove Partner To Deliver Subscription Programs To Retail Clients
Thursday, 1 Aug 2013 09:00am EDT
OrderGroove and eBay Enterprise, an eBay Inc. company announced a partnership to offer subscription programs to eBay Enterprise's vast network of omnichannel retail clients. eBay Enterprise had previously built their own subscription platform, but ultimately selected OrderGroove as a partner based on the company's technology and subscription practices and insights. Through the partnership, OrderGroove is integrating their Subscription Retail Platform with eBay Enterprise's commerce technology to help retailers tap into the power of convenience and turn new and existing customers into repeat buyers -- dramatically increasing sales and customer annual spend, building loyalty, maximizing lifetime value, and slashing customer defection rates. eBay Enterprise's pre-built integration of OrderGroove's subscription technology across its commerce platform will allow joint clients to quickly and efficiently: Maximize annual spend by increasing purchase frequency; Increase retention and the lifetime value of their customers; Reduce customer acquisition costs and price shopping comparison; Access OrderGroove's real-time subscription analytics, reports and customer service tools and Leverage impulse upsell and cross-sell opportunities to increaseaverage order value.Â 
